{{Quote|Records show that the ''Lucid Voice'' was dismantled at the Bilbringi shipyards four years ago.|A technician informs Moff Wilhuff Tarkin of the ''Lucid Voice''{{'s}} fate at Bilbringi|<ref name="Tarkin" />}}
'''Bilbringi''' was a [[Planet|world]]<ref name="Leia">''[[Leia, Princess of Alderaan]]''</ref> located in the [[Inner Rim Territories]].<ref name="TFABG" /> It was home to the [[Bilbringi shipyards]], a [[Shipyard|facility]] which dismantled the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Separatist]] [[Providence-class Dreadnought|dreadnought]] ''[[Lucid Voice]]'' within a [[Standard year|year]] after the end of the [[Clone Wars]].<ref name="Tarkin" /> The [[smuggler]] [[Han Solo]] was fond of Bilbringi [[Foodstuff|food]], and shared [[Cheese|cheesy]] meat [[pie]]s with [[pepper]] from Bilbringi with his [[Marriage|wife]], [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]], at their home on [[Hosnian Prime]] twenty-four years after the [[Battle of Endor]].<ref name="Bloodline">[[Bloodline (novel)|''Bloodline'']]</ref>

